{
  "stem": "20021.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But that was not so much for Zionistic reasons as for religious reasons.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And he lived in Tsfat and died there, was buried there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But then my uncle who was already a Zionist went to Israel in 1920s.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I have two aunts who went to Israel, joined a kibbutz.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And if they would come to visit, you know, it would be a real interesting affair.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "People would come to listen to their stories and so forth.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So Zionism played a big part in the community.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "My father went to Israel on a tour in 1932 and he came back.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And he lectured so many times and I would go with him, because people were so anxious to hear what Israel-- about Israel and so forth.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "In those days, people didn't have television, you have to remember, or radio, or even newspapers which would write about Israel, so it was very much word of mouth, somebody like that [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was-- we was all talking about it all the time, but you know, like probably next year or some time, or-- but not immediately, you know?",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then, of course, the war broke out and was too late.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we were not so much insulated, but anti-Semitism was very strong in Poland.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was at various level.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a little bit different with the so-called Polish intellectuals as it was with plain people.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was a large number of very uneducated people in Poland and so forth.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So the anti-Semitism might be exhibited in different ways.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But there was very strong anti-Semitism throughout the Polish society.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I felt it in various ways.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
